      "writtenOn": "2021-02-16T21:47:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think an alternative here is to have a field \"is_header\", and if a suggestion is a header, we can make it bold.\n\nSo this will become:\n{is_header: true, explanation: \u0027Filter Syntax\u0027}\n\nThe advantage is that it is a bit easier to read (i.e. we do not need to have a convention that value\u003d\u003d\u003dnull is header, and explanation can be pure string)\n\nI just feel a bit weird when in getIdQuerySuggestion we put the styling in \"display\", but here we incorporate it in explanation.",
      "revId": "167cad791f5c4ec5fa7ebbd5ff1bdc903f40ba3a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
